news.title: Builders with over 50 housing units to get doorstep MahaRERA registration
news.para: Speaking at the concluding ceremony of the Credai-organised ‘Dalan 2024’ exhibition in Kolhapur on Wednesday, Devara said state govt aims to increase annual revenue generation through stamp duty registrations.

news.title: Godrej Properties acquires about 12.5-acre land parcel in Hyderabad
news.para: The development on this land is estimated to have a potential of approximately 4 million sq ft of saleable area comprising primarily of residential apartments with an estimated revenue potential of about Rs 3,500 crore.

news.title: Oyo Hotels & Homes may back out of IPO plan, opt for private raise
news.para: In a response to emailed queries by ET, Oyo said the information is inaccurate. Oyo’s first public offer filing was returned by the markets regulator in January 2023, requiring the SoftBank-backed firm to refile its draft red herring prospectus (DRHP) with updates and revisions.

news.title: Phoenix Mills records 69% rise in net profit at Rs 297 crore in Q3 FY24
news.para: Retail collections rose 30% to Rs 700 crore, while rental income from retail grew 33% to Rs 447 crore. Operating profit in retail business increased 27% to over Rs 435 crore. The company’s malls are operating at life-time high leased occupancy and trading levels.

news.title: Radius Group's MD denied bail in money laundering case
news.para: ​​​​​​​​The ED has accused Chhabria of playing a crucial role in diverting funds procured illegally by Yes Bank's founder Rana Kapoor and Dewan Housing Finance Limited (DHFL) promoter Kapil Wadhawan.

news.title: NCLT dismisses lawsuit demanding probe into affairs of Indiabulls Housing
news.para: Supertech Realtors alleged that Indiabulls Housing Finance had illegally deducted excess sums of money from its loan account.  In its lawsuit, the real estate firm alleged that the total sum accrued to it was ₹5,873 crore but Indiabulls Housing Finance deducted ₹6,150 crore from its loan account.

news.title: James Hardie’s net profit rise 39% to 179.9 million in Q3 FY24
news.para: The Dublin-based firm's adjusted net income for the three months ended Dec. 31 was $179.9 million, compared with $129.2 million last year.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram: HC verdict on Dragonstone Realty's project likely in two weeks
news.para: Sources said the hearing proceedings related to the petition have been completed. The court’s judgment is crucial for the project, as it will have an impact on its future expansion in its non-SEZ component.

news.title: When it comes to high street space, more is less: Tanuj Bhargava, Chief Leasing Officer of Fairfox Group, Noida, Sector 140A
news.para: Bharat’s high street space is set to expand substantially from Metro Cities to Tier II and Tier III cities. Nurtured seasoned developers are looking to develop about three million square feet of retail projects with open spaces in the next 2-3 years.

news.title: PM to lay foundation of Gurugram Metro on February 16
news.para: The Union Cabinet approved the project which proposes to provide metro connectivity from Huda City Centre to Cyber City with a spur to Dwarka Expressway.

news.title: MCC intensifies efforts to collect property tax in Mysuru
news.para: At the end of Jan, the MCC has achieved 80% of its target, collecting Rs 170.8 crore in property taxes. It includes arrears of 2023-24. The target it has set is Rs 214.1 crore.

news.title: Maharashtra seeks information about plots available for lease in seven cantonments
news.para: The DMA has also told the cantonments to collate information about civic facilities, infrastructure, number of serving and retired employees, financial status and citizens’ views on the merger plans.

news.title: Navi Mumbai residents fume as open dumpers loaded with construction debris go unchecked
news.para: Earlier, the civic body had issued diktats to stop open vehicles from carrying debris from construction sites and warned of strict action against perpetrators.

news.title: SC refuses to interfere with HCs' orders in Indiabulls Housing's case
news.para: Supreme Court on Monday refused to entertain a PIL challenging validity of the Criminal Procedure (Identification) Act, 2022 which allows collection of various biometric measurements of accused, and allowed the petitioner to approach high court.

news.title: Kesoram Industries plans to raise funds from Tata Capital to refinance its Rs 1,500-crore debt
news.para: The company is looking for a one-year finance before the asset moves to UltraTech following regulatory clearances, they said, adding that Kesoram is looking to refinance the debt at 12-13%. Talks for the new loan could close by the end of this month, Kesoram Industries added.

news.title: DTCP demolishes 100 structures in 12 illegal colonies in Gurugram
news.para: The move comes three days after DTCP started surveying colonies across the city to check if any rules have or are being violated. The drives were conducted in 12 illegal colonies.

news.title: Greater Noida: Five years after NCLT's move, 850 RG Luxury Homes' buyers get flats
news.para: Around 850 homebuyers of a condominium in Greater Noida West will get their homes, five years after filing a case at the National Company Law Tribunal when all they could see at the project site were the bare concrete frames of towers.
